-- Indian shares end lower after hitting record high
-- By Indulal PM
-- Fri Apr 25, 2014 06:10AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, April 25 (Reuters) - Indian shares ended lower after hitting a record high for the fourth straight session on disappointment over earnings from market heavyweights including ICICI Bank Ltd <ICBK.NS>.

The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> provisionally closed down 0.82 percent at 22,688.07. The index rose as much as 0.27 percent to an all-time high of 22,939.31 earlier the day. The broader NSE index <.NSEI> ended 0.85 percent lower at 6,782.75 after gaining as much as 0.42 percent to a record high of 6,869.85 earlier the session.